The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation using deep neural networks and focuses on image-to-image translation as a means of regularizing the features extracted by the encoder network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel use of unpaired image-to-image translation, which involves training a generator network to translate images from one domain to another without paired examples. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also applies the proposed method to classification and segmentation tasks, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories as well.
